data.description: Here it is…that hard to find, Penn Harris Madison home with a main floor master suite. The home is located on the Southside of South Bend in Staffordshire Estates close to shopping, the St. Joe County Fairgrounds, the by-pass and just minutes to campus.  The subdivision which offers sidewalks, city water & sewer with the lower county tax rate. You enter this home through a 2-story foyer with beautiful Brazilian Cherrywood flooring that runs through the formal dining room, kitchen, informal dining area and framing the great room. The focal point of the home is the great room with its soaring 17’ ceiling palladium windows flanking the cozy gas fireplace. The open concept floor plan aids large gatherings.  The kitchen is a chef’s dream with its Corian countertops, undermount sink, beautiful cherry cabinets, an island that features a breakfast bar, and stainless-steel appliances created for homeowners who love to cook and entertain.  The informal dining area has plenty of light with accent windows surrounding the patio door leading to a lovely composite deck with wisteria and trumpet vines that grow up the trellis to create privacy.  The exterior of the home offers a quaint manageable yard with an abundance of perennials that will keep you surprised all Spring & Summer with their beauty. The 1st floor master suite includes a walk-in closet through the bathroom that has a double vanity, soaking tub, separate shower, and private commode. Upstairs you will find a multi-use 7 x 10 loft area perfect for a study nook, 2 bedrooms and the 2nd full bath.  The finished basement is to die for and includes a 17 x 21 living area, 4th bedroom with egress window, a 3rd. full bath and a spare room for crafts or a workout room.  There is also plenty of room in the unfinished portion of the basement for storage. Garage door recently replace in 2021.  Photos with furnishings are virtually staged.
